The Emir of Katsina, Alhaji Abdulmumini Kabir, has directed the 45 district heads under the Katsina Emirate Council to establish security committees in order to checkmate insecurity in the emirate. The emir gave the directive yesterday at a meeting with the district heads in his palace. “The district heads should collaborate with village and wards heads in their domain to provide information to security agents in their areas. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “They should provide all the necessary assistance to security agents to enable them discharge their duties effectively. “The Katsina emirate council will do everything possible to checkmate the security challenges facing the area,’’ Kabir said. He called on people in his domain including those at the grassroots to provide information to the traditional rulers on the movement of suspected persons. “It is the duty of the local people to provide information about strangers in their communities to district or village heads for action. “No stranger will reside in a community without the consent or permission of the district or village head under the emirate council,” he said. (NAN) Katsina emirate gets new kingmakers Masari promises to complete District Heads residences soon Yobe monarch advocates jail term for parents who refuse to enroll kids in school Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin